# ── How a wallet reaches your KERIA (OOBI host) ─────────────────────────
# A wallet that scans an OOBI must be able to REACH KERIA over the network.
# Pick ONE of the two setups below.

# ---- Option A: automatic public tunnel (default, no domain needed) ----
# Opens an ngrok tunnel and advertises its public https URL in OOBIs.
# NOTE: a FREE random tunnel gets a NEW url on every restart — fine for a quick
# test, but a stored wallet connection breaks each time. For anything ongoing,
# reserve a static domain (below).
COMPOSE_PROFILES=tunnel
KERIA_PUBLIC_URL=ngrok
# Free token: https://dashboard.ngrok.com/get-started/your-authtoken
NGROK_AUTHTOKEN=

# ---- Option A+: reserved static ngrok domain (stable url) ----
# Reserve one at https://dashboard.ngrok.com/domains, then set BOTH (with the
# https:// scheme on KERIA_PUBLIC_URL):
#   KERIA_PUBLIC_URL=https://your-name.ngrok-free.dev
#   NGROK_DOMAIN=your-name.ngrok-free.dev
# The url never changes, so the wallet connection survives restarts.

# ---- Option B: your own domain ----
# Point a domain at this host's port 3902, then set:
#   COMPOSE_PROFILES=          (empty — no tunnel)
#   KERIA_PUBLIC_URL=https://keria.yourdomain.org
#   NGROK_AUTHTOKEN=           (unused)

# ---- Local only (no wallet) ----
# Leave both COMPOSE_PROFILES and KERIA_PUBLIC_URL empty for internal-only dev;
# the stack runs but a wallet cannot connect.
